<h1><i class="far fa-file"></i>Viewing Hidden Items</h1>

<ol class="breadcrumb">
	<li><a href="#help"><i class="fa fa-question-circle"></i>Help</a></li>
	<li><a href="#help/working-with-files"><i class="fa fa-file"></i>Working with Files</a></li>
	<li><i class="fa fa-file"></i>Viewing Hidden Items</li>
</ol>

<div class="content">
	<p><%= application.name %> allows you to hide and show files and folders and certain details about them in order to make the <a href="#apps/file-browser">File Browser</a> display as clear as possible. </p>

	<ol>
		<li>
			<h2><i class="far fa-file"></i>Hidden Files</h2>
			<p>By selecting "Hidden Files" on the View menu, you can display system files and folders (items that have names that start with a dot).  For example, the folder '.thumbs' and the files '.htaccess' and '.DS_Store' are common system files.  System files are hidden by default. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img class="dropdown menu" src="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-hidden-items/show-hidden-menu-item@2x.png" />
				<div class="caption">"Hidden Files" on the View Menu</div>
			</div>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-hidden-items/hidden-files.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Show Hidden Files and Folders (.Clipboard and .thumbs)"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-hidden-items/hidden-files.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Show Hidden Files and Folders (.Clipboard and .thumbs)</div>
			</div>

			<div class="tip well">
				<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-lightbulb"></i></span>Tip</h3><p>You can quickly hide or show hidden items using the keyboard shortcut: command or control + dot(.).</p>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-image"></i>Thumbnails</h2>
			<p>Graphical files such as images and .pdf documents are normally be displayed using a tiny image of the item called a "thumbnail".  By selecting "Thumbnails" on the View menu, you can hide and show these thumbnail preview images.  When thumbnails are not shown, an icon for the particular file type is shown instead. Thumbnails are shown by default. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img class="dropdown menu" src="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-hidden-items/show-thumbnails-menu-item@2x.png" />
				<div class="caption">"Thumbnails" on the View Menu</div>
			</div>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-hidden-items/no-thumbs.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Hide Thumbnails (for image files and .pdf files)"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-hidden-items/no-thumbs.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Hide Thumbnails (for image files and .pdf files)</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-file"></i>File Extensions</h2>
			<p>By selecting "File Extensions" on the View menu, you can hide and show file extensions (the part of the file name after the dot). File extensions are hidden by default. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img class="dropdown menu" src="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-hidden-items/show-file-extensions-menu-item@2x.png" />
				<div class="caption">"File Extensions" on the View Menu</div>
			</div>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-hidden-items/file-extensions.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Show File Extensions"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-hidden-items/file-extensions.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Show File Extensions</div>
			</div>
		</li>
	</ol>
</div>